        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Norton Commander'); ?>
        <p><strong>Norton Commander</strong> (commonly shortened to "<strong>NC</strong>" by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DOS', 'OS'); ?> users, due to its filename <code>NC.exe</code>) was a prototypical orthodox file manager (OFM), written by <strong>John Socha</strong> and released by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Peter Norton Computing', 'C'); ?> (later acquired in 1990 by the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Symantec Corporation', 'C'); ?>).</p>
        <p>NC is a file manager which provides a text user interface on top of DOS.</p>
        <p>It was officially produced between 1986 and 1998. The last DOS version of Norton Commander, 5.51, was released on 1 July 1998.</p>
        <p>A related product, <strong>Norton Desktop</strong>, a graphical shell for DOS and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows', 'OS'); ?>, succeeded Norton Commander. It came in two variants, Norton Desktop for DOS (NDD) and Norton Desktop for Windows (NDW).</p>
